Hello, I am a client of BBVA and I would like to share my terrible experience with this bank. I had to leave Spain for a year and needed to change my phone number through which I could confirm transfers. First I was told that I couldn't have a non-Spanish number and also there was no alternative way of making transfers other than using my Spanish number. Then, I was told I could use a foreign number but needed to change it at my branch (how could that possibly be done once someone has left the country to obtain their new number?). Finally, after a month of phone calls and struggling with operators telling me nothing could be done and my money would remain inaccessible, my number was changed to an Australian one. However, right now I can't make a single transfer from my account and keep receiving error messages. To sum up: my money is blocked in my Spanish account and it seems that there isn't a single person at BBVA who knows what they are doing. I would not recommend this bank to anyone ever.
